                <updated>Fri, 9 May 2014 20:07:59 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Fri, 9 May 2014 20:07:59 +0000</resolved>
                                                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>5</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="83670" author="rhenwood" created="Fri, 9 May 2014 20:07:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This got closed with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-108&quot; title=&quot;configure --prefix broken for libcfs.ko on master&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-108&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-108&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76665" author="jessica" created="Mon, 10 Feb 2014 22:21:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Richard - &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should this ticket be assigned to Di and tracked as part of DNE deliverables?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;-Jessica&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="75614" author="adilger" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 23:44:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also be useful to have a paragraph or six that provides an overview of the DNE Phase 1 functionality, in particular describing that it is mostly intended for administrator use (and by default limited only to administrators), only provides static directory distribution, that there is not yet a migration tool besides &quot;copy all data&quot;, etc.  This could easily be copy-pasted from the Project Scope, Solution Architecture, and/or HLD into the manual.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="75610" author="adilger" created="Fri, 24 Jan 2014 23:00:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are a couple of gaps in the user manual related to DNE Phase 1:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the glossary should define &quot;DNE&quot; since this is what users know the feature as&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;it might make sense to use DNE in a few places where multiple MDTs are described, so that this is more easily found in the manual.  As it stands, there is no one place to find out about DNE in the manual.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;add &quot;lfs mkdir&quot; to the UserUtilities section, per &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4237&quot; title=&quot;Update lfs man page to include lfs mkdir&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4237&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4237&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="53105" author="rhenwood" created="Wed, 27 Feb 2013 04:58:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This ticket is a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-108&quot; title=&quot;add documentation for DNE&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-108&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-108&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-108&quot; title=&quot;add documentation for DNE&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LUDOC-108&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUDOC-108&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is closed as complete.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46480" author="adilger" created="Fri, 12 Oct 2012 14:35:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Update the user manual to describe changes to the user tools:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;formatting, mounting, usage, configuration, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;potentially some of the example output (if relevant to the examples)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;/proc tunables, module parameters, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Since we use a single manual for all of the Lustre releases, when changing any significant sections of text the content should include the version in which the change was made (i.e. 2.4) and leave the old comments in place (at least back to 2.1, older 1.x sections can be removed), for example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Starting with Lustre 2.4, it is possible to add multiple MDTs to a single Lustre filesystem, by specifying a non-zero index for the later MDTs, like &lt;tt&gt;mkfs.lustre --mdt --index 1 ... /dev/mdt0001&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
</comment>
